---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon — Sam Stringer-Hye" description="How this site was built.">
  <section class="colophon-page">
    <div class="colophon-header">
      <p class="typo-caption" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">About this site</p>
      <h1 class="typo-headline">Colophon</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="colophon-body" data-reveal="fade-up">
      <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
      <p>
        Built with <strong>Astro</strong> for static-first delivery with selective React hydration for interactive components.
        3D hero animation rendered with <strong>Three.js</strong>.
        Animations powered by <strong>GSAP</strong> (ScrollTrigger, Draggable, SplitText).
        Smooth scrolling via <strong>Lenis</strong>. Deployed on <strong>Vercel</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Typography</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Inter</strong> by Rasmus Andersson — a typeface designed for computer screens with a tall x-height for legibility at small sizes.
        All text uses regular weight (400); hierarchy is expressed through size alone.
      </p>

      <h2>Design Language</h2>
      <p>
        The prismatic/CMY (cyan, magenta, yellow) chromatic separation is used throughout as a unifying visual language.
        It appears in scroll reveals, hover effects, the hero animation's temporal RGB split, and the carousel's velocity-driven shadows.
        This references how white light splits through a prism — a metaphor for breaking a design system into its constituent parts.
      </p>

      <h2>Accessibility</h2>
      <p>
        This site respects <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> — all animations are disabled or minimized when the user has requested reduced motion.
        Navigation is fully keyboard-accessible, the about modal includes a focus trap, and all images include alt text.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .colophon-page {
    max-width: var(--container-content);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--page-padding);
  }

  .colophon-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .colophon-header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
  }

  .colophon-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    line-height: var(--line-height-normal);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-normal);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
  }

  .colophon-body h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .colophon-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans-serif);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-sans-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--line-height-normal);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-normal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .colophon-body strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .colophon-body code {
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    padding: var(--radius-sm) var(--space-1);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }
</style>
